Jupyter Python Course

This notebook contains exercises and coding challenges from a Python course using Jupyter Notebooks. It covers a wide range of topics from basic syntax to intermediate concepts.

Contents
- Python Basics
- Data Structures (Lists, Tuples, Dictionaries)
- Conditional Statements and Loops
- Functions and Recursion
- File Handling
- Error and Exception Handling
- Basic Data Analysis Concepts

How to Run
1. Install [Jupyter Notebook](https://jupyter.org/install) using Anaconda or pip.
2. Ensure Python 3 is installed.
3. Open the notebook using the following command:
    ```bash
    jupyter notebook Jupyter_course_modified.ipynb
    ```

Notes
- Explanations and code explanations are added for better clarity.
- You are encouraged to tweak and experiment with the code to build a solid understanding.
